cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision datasets and proposes a training methodology to take advantage of additional modalities available in datasets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a technique that combines with existing deep convolutional architectures, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with object tracking and pedestrian detection, which could be relevant to the categories cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
